max agro a spell could generate was 800pts prior to expansion.  Ch, big nukes, all of it was 800 according to some knowledgable people ive talked to.<br>
<br>
<br>
now im just pointing out lets say there is a max agro a CH/nuke can generate.  If your nuke is over it and the druid nuke is under it who can do more damage?  the one that is doing the same ratio damage but generating less agro thats who.   the druid nuke mentioned here will suffer every point of damage as agro. the ice based wizard nuke supposedly drew a max agro of 800pts according to the peeps i talked to.  free damage no agro after that.  <br>
<br>
still mad?<br>
<br>
ya if your thinking from a solo point of view.  but from a raid point of view ill believe a druid using little nukes can push out the same damage as a wizard using big nukes when i see it.  i expect to see one dead druid that trys.<br>
