<br>
<br>
Mages and Wizards are, and have been for awhile, balanced against each other. Mages are ment to have long term damage, but be able to go into burst mode if needed. Wizards, well Wizards are ment to be able to get that 5000 damage in when and where it is needed.<br>
<br>
I think Mage damage should outdo Rogue damage. Mages have no way (Concussion, Evade, Jolt), of lowering aggro. So, our Magical damage abilities are limited by aggro more than any other class (perhaps equal with Druids).<br>
<br>
Firebolt of Tallon, its a great spell. In fact, I agree, a Level 61 Vendor bought spell should not hold it's power. However, in the long run I don't think its overpowered. Wizards get better ratios 61+, and the FoT is a bolt, which holds some disadvantages.<br>
<br>
Only a few of us Mages are whiners. And we usually comment them down in threads nowadays. The T-Rod nerf hit some people hard. But I think we all are very happy with our current situation, no more rod slavery.  <p>&quot;History is just a set of lies agreed upon&quot; - Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte<br>
